-- Scotland, Denmark Open World Cup Qualifying With Home Ties
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-09-08T20:20:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-08/scotland-denmark-open-world-cup-qualifying-with-home-ties.html
Scotland and Denmark both played 0-0
ties at home in their opening European qualifying matches for
the 2014 soccer  World Cup .  Scotland drew with Serbia at Hampden Park in Glasgow in a
Group A match, while Denmark and the  Czech Republic  finished
goalless in Copenhagen.  Last night, Belgium beat Wales 2-0 and Croatia defeated
Macedonia 1-0 in Group A matches, while Armenia defeated Malta
1-0 and Bulgaria and Italy played a 2-2 tie in Group B.  The next round of European matches will be played Sept. 11.
Among the 24 schedule games, world champion Spain begins its
qualifying campaign by visiting Georgia.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
